# SYS-LIC-RRM
## Replay Recovery Manager

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-RRM serves as the recovery orchestration controller for the HyperSync License Operating System.

Its responsibility is to monitor replay candidates, evaluate recovery eligibility, schedule bounded retry attempts, coordinate replay dispatch, and preserve complete operational telemetry throughout the recovery lifecycle.

Rather than functioning as a simple retry scheduler, SYS-LIC-RRM provides deterministic recovery management designed to maximize operational resiliency while preventing duplicate execution and uncontrolled retry behavior.

---

# Architectural Purpose

SYS-LIC-RRM is responsible for:

• Recovery Orchestration

• Replay Queue Management

• Replay Eligibility Evaluation

• Exponential Backoff Scheduling

• Registry Verification

• Replay Dispatch Coordination

• Recovery Telemetry

• Governance Evidence Generation

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs the following operational sequence:

- Execute scheduled recovery cycle
- Scan replay queue
- Evaluate replay eligibility
- Calculate bounded retry schedule
- Verify authoritative registry state
- Coordinate replay dispatch
- Record recovery telemetry
- Append immutable governance evidence

Each recovery attempt follows a deterministic operational contract.

